&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;QE Facilities Ltd is a wholly owned subsidiary company of Gateshead Health NHS Foundation Trust.  QEF is a separate legal body which provides a range of non-clinical, high quality Estates and Facilities services. QEF has been established on the solid foundations of the NHS and is in the unique position to be able to provide a flexible, pro-active range of services as an independent commercial organisation, delivering significant savings and efficiencies to NHS organisations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Estates Department: Architectural Technician&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;REF. NO:  297-QEF221-20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours: 37.5 per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Location: Darlington Memorial Hospital, Hollyhurst Rd, Darlington&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration: Grade D - £37,910 p.a.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Architectural Technician to join the estates / maintenance team at QE Facilities Limited. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;The position will be based at Darlington Memorial Hospital, Darlington, County Durham. However, you may be required to carry out work at any other site maintained by QE Facilities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role of Architectural Technician will produce sketch designs, concept designs, working drawings, project management, costing and specifications, and coordinate site control of Capital Works projects undertaken by the Company, on the Darlington Memorial Hospital site. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The successful candidate will need to fulfil the essential criteria for this position. They must have a good working knowledge of Building Regulations, Codes of Practice and standard forms of contract,&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;project cost estimation, tender specification and analysis, and the use of AutoCad system or equivalent.  You will also be familiar with relevant legislation, Guidance Notes, Health Technical Memoranda, Health Building Notes, building related Codes of Practice, together with technical and operational documents relevant to the Estates function.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be able to work and act on your own initiative and possess the ability to communicate effectively and collaboratively, with all customers, users and staff. You should be self-motivated, with extensive relevant post-qualification experience of the building process, in particular the design, detailing, specification and construction of building projects. A flexible attitude is required to succeed within the Company, as is a desire to deliver excellent customer service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is subject to DBS (Police Bureau) standard disclosure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal enquiries are welcomed by Stu Stangroom on 01325 743894&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
